Fix TypeError when contrib restructures the multiple-value form header.

claro_preprocess_field_multiple_value_form() guards the header-cell class
manipulation with isset() only, then calls ->removeClass() on it. When the
Paragraphs multi-value widget (e.g. the Gallery block's field_gallery_items)
restructures the header so that #attributes is a plain array rather than an
Attribute object, this fatals with 'Call to a member function removeClass()
on array' (white screen when adding the block in Layout Builder).

Type-guard the branch with 'instanceof Attribute' so Claro skips its
cosmetic label classes for a contrib-restructured header instead of
crashing, matching the existing instanceof Attribute idiom in this file.

Ref: https://www.drupal.org/project/drupal/issues/3099026
     https://www.drupal.org/project/paragraphs/issues/3099024

--- a/core/themes/claro/claro.theme
+++ b/core/themes/claro/claro.theme
@@ -1075,7 +1075,7 @@
     // Add an additional CSS class to the field label table cell. The table
     // header cell should always exist unless removed by contrib.
     // @see template_preprocess_field_multiple_value_form().
-    if (isset($variables['table']['#header'][0]['data']['#attributes'])) {
+    if (isset($variables['table']['#header'][0]['data']['#attributes']) && $variables['table']['#header'][0]['data']['#attributes'] instanceof Attribute) {
       $variables['table']['#header'][0]['data']['#attributes']->removeClass('label');
       $variables['table']['#header'][0]['data']['#attributes']->addClass('form-item__label', 'form-item__label--multiple-value-form');
     }
